00:14:20.830 --> 00:14:23.930
with lullaby, lullaby, lullaby.

273
00:14:24.500 --> 00:14:25.700
Hence, away.

274
00:14:25.700 --> 00:14:27.570
Now all is well.

275
00:14:27.570 --> 00:14:30.830
One aloof stand sentinel.

276
00:14:40.430 --> 00:14:42.300
What thou seest when thou dostwake,

277
00:14:42.300 --> 00:14:45.200
do it for thy true-love take,

278
00:14:45.200 --> 00:14:48.470
love and languish for his sake,

279
00:14:48.470 --> 00:14:52.400
be it ounce, or cat, or bear,pard,

280
00:14:52.400 --> 00:14:53.970
or boar with bristled hair

281
00:14:53.970 --> 00:14:56.530
in thy eye that shall appearwhen thou wakest,

282
00:14:56.530 --> 00:14:59.670
it is thy dear.

283
00:15:03.800 --> 00:15:07.170
Wake when some vile thing isnear.

284
00:15:10.700 --> 00:15:14.730
Fair love, you faint withwandering in the wood.

285
00:15:14.730 --> 00:15:19.430
And to speak troth, I haveforgot our way.

286
00:15:23.600 --> 00:15:26.100
We'll rest us, Hermia, if youthink it good,

287
00:15:26.100 --> 00:15:28.570
and tarry for the comfort of theday.

288
00:15:28.570 --> 00:15:30.300
Be it so, Lysander.

289
00:15:30.300 --> 00:15:34.030
Find you out a bed, for I uponthis bank will rest my head.

290
00:15:34.030 --> 00:15:36.300
One turf shall serve as pillowfor us both,

291
00:15:36.300 --> 00:15:40.500
one heart, one bed, two bosomsand one troth.

292
00:15:40.500 --> 00:15:42.470
Nay, good Lysander,

293
00:15:43.600 --> 00:15:46.100
for my sake, my dear, liefurther off.

294
00:15:46.100 --> 00:15:47.500
Do not lie so near.

295
00:15:47.500 --> 00:15:55.400
Oh, take the sense, sweet, of myinnocence.

296
00:15:55.400 --> 00:15:58.070
Love takes the meaning in love'sconference.

297
00:15:58.070 --> 00:16:01.630
I mean, that my heart unto yoursis knit

298
00:16:01.630 --> 00:16:05.770
so that one heart we can make ofit,

299
00:16:05.770 --> 00:16:08.570
two bosoms interchained with anoath

300
00:16:08.570 --> 00:16:13.770
so then two bosoms and a singletroth.

301
00:16:13.770 --> 00:16:16.000
Then by your side no bedroom medeny.

302
00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:20.700
For lying so, Hermia, I do notlie.

303
00:16:20.700 --> 00:16:22.700
Lysander riddles very prettily.

304
00:16:22.700 --> 00:16:25.130
Now much beshrew my manners andmy pride

305
00:16:25.130 --> 00:16:27.170
if Hermia meant to say Lysanderlied.

306
00:16:27.170 --> 00:16:31.670
But, gentle friend, for love andcourtesy lie further off.

307
00:16:31.670 --> 00:16:33.300
In human modesty,

308
00:16:33.300 --> 00:16:36.730
such separation as may well besaid

309
00:16:36.730 --> 00:16:40.370
becomes a virtuous bachelor anda maid.

310
00:16:40.370 --> 00:16:42.770
So far be distant.

311
00:16:42.770 --> 00:16:44.930
And, good night, sweet friend.

312
00:16:44.930 --> 00:16:50.030
Thy love ne'er alter till thysweet life end.

313
00:16:58.870 --> 00:17:04.770
Amen, amen to that fair prayer,say I.

314
00:17:04.770 --> 00:17:08.400
So end life when I end loyalty.

315
00:17:18.330 --> 00:17:19.630
Here is my bed.

316
00:17:22.670 --> 00:17:25.400
Sleep give thee all his rest.

317
00:17:25.400 --> 00:17:28.600
With half that wish, thewisher's eyes be pressed.

318
00:17:31.500 --> 00:17:33.900
Through the forest have I gone,

319
00:17:33.900 --> 00:17:37.400
but Athenian found I none onwhose eyes I might approve

320
00:17:37.400 --> 00:17:41.000
this flower's force in stirringlove.

321
00:17:41.000 --> 00:17:42.970
Night and silence.

322
00:17:42.970 --> 00:17:44.100
Who is here?

323
00:17:44.100 --> 00:17:46.830
Weeds of Athens he doth wear.

324
00:17:46.830 --> 00:17:52.970
This is he, my master said,despised the Athenian maid.

325
00:17:52.970 --> 00:17:58.400
And here the maiden sleepingsound on the dank and dirtyground.

326
00:17:58.400 --> 00:17:59.700
Pretty soul,

327
00:17:59.700 --> 00:18:04.100
She durst not lie near thislack-love, this kill-courtesy.

328
00:18:04.100 --> 00:18:10.130
Churl, upon thy eyes I throw allthe power this charm doth owe.

329
00:18:10.130 --> 00:18:13.430
When thou wakest, let loveforbid.

330
00:18:13.430 --> 00:18:17.170
Sleep his seat on thy eyelid.

331
00:18:17.170 --> 00:18:21.170
So awake when I am gone, for Imust now to Oberon.

332
00:18:21.170 --> 00:18:24.100
Stay, though thou kill me, sweetDemetrius.

333
00:18:27.330 --> 00:18:30.730
I charge thee, hence, and do nothaunt me thus.

334
00:18:30.730 --> 00:18:32.300
Oh, wilt thou darkling leave me?

335
00:18:32.300 --> 00:18:33.500
Do not so.

336
00:18:33.500 --> 00:18:35.000
Stay, on thy peril.

337
00:18:37.030 --> 00:18:38.670
I alone will go.

338
00:18:51.530 --> 00:18:58.500
Oh, I am out of breath in thisfond chase.

339
00:18:58.500 --> 00:19:01.500
The more my prayer, the lesseris my grace.

340
00:19:03.870 --> 00:19:07.000
Happy is Hermia, wheresoe'er shelies,

341
00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:10.570
for she hath blessed andattractive eyes.

342
00:19:12.770 --> 00:19:15.330
How came her eyes so bright?

343
00:19:15.330 --> 00:19:18.370
Not with salt tears.

344
00:19:18.370 --> 00:19:20.630
If so, my eyes are oftenerwashed than hers.

345
00:19:28.570 --> 00:19:36.230
No, no, I am as ugly as a bear.

346
00:19:36.230 --> 00:19:39.900
For beasts that meet me run awayfor fear.

347
00:19:39.900 --> 00:19:43.030
Therefore no marvel thoughDemetrius do

348
00:19:43.030 --> 00:19:45.930
as a monster fly my presencethus.

349
00:19:45.930 --> 00:19:49.370
What wicked and dissemblingglass of mine

350
00:19:49.370 --> 00:19:52.300
made me compare with Hermia'ssphery eyne?

351
00:19:57.030 --> 00:19:58.230
But who is here?

352
00:20:00.700 --> 00:20:02.870
Lysander on the ground!

353
00:20:02.870 --> 00:20:04.430
Dead?

354
00:20:04.430 --> 00:20:07.230
Or asleep?

355
00:20:07.230 --> 00:20:09.930
I see no blood, no wound.

356
00:20:09.930 --> 00:20:13.470
Lysander, if you live, good sir,awake.

357
00:20:13.470 --> 00:20:16.700
And run through fire will I forthy sweet sake.

358
00:20:16.700 --> 00:20:19.230
Transparent Helena!

359
00:20:19.230 --> 00:20:22.470
Nature shows art,

360
00:20:22.470 --> 00:20:25.630
that through thy bosom makes mesee thy heart.

361
00:20:25.630 --> 00:20:27.830
Where is Demetrius?

362
00:20:27.830 --> 00:20:32.170
Oh, how fit a word is that vilename to perish on my sword.

363
00:20:32.170 --> 00:20:35.900
Do not say so, Lysander.

364
00:20:35.900 --> 00:20:40.500
Say not so what though he loveyour Hermia?

365
00:20:40.500 --> 00:20:41.870
Lord, what though?

366
00:20:41.870 --> 00:20:45.070
Yet Hermia still loves you, thenbe content.

367
00:20:45.070 --> 00:20:48.130
Content with Hermia.

368
00:20:48.130 --> 00:20:54.730
No, I do repent the tediousminutes I with her have spent.

369
00:20:54.730 --> 00:20:58.400
Not Hermia but Helena I love.

370
00:20:58.400 --> 00:21:02.600
Who will not change a raven fora dove?

371
00:21:02.600 --> 00:21:06.330
The will of man is by his reasonswayed.

372
00:21:06.330 --> 00:21:08.300
And reason says you are theworthier maid.

373
00:21:08.300 --> 00:21:11.100
Things growing are not ripeuntil their season,

374
00:21:11.100 --> 00:21:14.270
so I, being young, till now ripenot to reason.

375
00:21:14.270 --> 00:21:18.200
And touching now the point ofhuman skill,

376
00:21:18.200 --> 00:21:20.300
reason becomes the marshal to mywill

377
00:21:20.300 --> 00:21:23.870
and leads me to your eyes,

378
00:21:27.530 --> 00:21:31.630
where I o'erlook love's storieswritten in love's richest book.

379
00:21:33.830 --> 00:21:37.930
Wherefore was I to this keenmockery born?

380
00:21:39.730 --> 00:21:42.800
When at your hand did I deservethis scorn?

381
00:21:42.800 --> 00:21:46.230
It's not enough-- it's notenough, young man,

382
00:21:46.230 --> 00:21:49.330
that I did never, no, nor nevercan,

383
00:21:49.330 --> 00:21:51.730
deserve a sweet look fromDemetrius' eye,

384
00:21:51.730 --> 00:21:54.070
but you must flout myinsufficiency?

385
00:21:54.070 --> 00:21:55.370
Good troth, you do me wrong.

386
00:21:55.370 --> 00:21:59.630
Good sooth, you do, in suchdisdainful manner me to woo.

387
00:21:59.630 --> 00:22:01.370
But fare you well.

388
00:22:01.370 --> 00:22:04.770
Perforce, I must confess

389
00:22:04.770 --> 00:22:10.730
I thought you lord of more truegentleness.

390
00:22:10.730 --> 00:22:13.470
Oh, that a lady, of one manrefused

391
00:22:13.470 --> 00:22:16.200
