396
00:22:33.230 --> 00:22:36.970
to honour Helen and to be herknight.

397
00:22:42.070 --> 00:22:43.700
Ay me, for pity!

398
00:22:43.700 --> 00:22:46.800
What a dream was here.

399
00:22:46.800 --> 00:22:49.230
Lysander, look how I do quakewith fear.

400
00:22:49.230 --> 00:22:53.770
Methought a serpent ate my heartaway

401
00:22:53.770 --> 00:22:58.700
and you sat smiling at his cruelpray.

402
00:22:58.700 --> 00:23:00.400
Lysander?

403
00:23:08.900 --> 00:23:10.570
What, removed?

404
00:23:13.230 --> 00:23:14.500
Lysander!

405
00:23:18.200 --> 00:23:19.670
Lord!

406
00:23:22.600 --> 00:23:23.870
What, out of hearing?

407
00:23:23.870 --> 00:23:25.270
Gone?

408
00:23:27.030 --> 00:23:29.700
No sound,

409
00:23:29.700 --> 00:23:31.230
no word?

410
00:23:32.970 --> 00:23:34.770
Alack, where are you?

411
00:23:34.770 --> 00:23:37.970
Speak, and if you hear,

412
00:23:37.970 --> 00:23:40.230
speak, of all loves.

413
00:23:40.230 --> 00:23:42.000
I swoon almost with fear.

414
00:23:44.530 --> 00:23:47.170
No?

415
00:23:47.170 --> 00:23:51.930
Then I well perceive you are notnigh.

416
00:23:51.930 --> 00:23:59.300
Either death or you I'll findimmediately.

